# Icons

Always use `react-icons` for any icon. Never use inline SVGs, emoji, or other icon libraries.

Install if needed:
```bash
npm install react-icons
```

## Usage

Import from the appropriate icon pack sub-path:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { FiArrowRight, FiMenu } from "react-icons/fi";
import { FaGithub } from "react-icons/fa";

<FiArrowRight className="w-5 h-5" />

// ❌ BAD — inline SVG
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" ...>...</svg>

// ❌ BAD — emoji as icon
<span>→</span>
```

Pick the most semantically appropriate icon pack (e.g. `fi` for Feather, `fa` for Font Awesome, `md` for Material Design, `hi` for Heroicons).
